column5: My friends at Golden Eagle Camp said they were gonna come to visit with some atvrs from atvnation.com....	what a great bunch of people 19 or 20.... brought cookies!! I hauled some pike outta the river and did up a fish fry for them, plus they were pretty wet and cold, so we bucked the stove..... It was quite interesting to meet people doing a g2g from another whole community... its nice to know that OFC is not alone in our type of endeavours.
Looks like a party!
That's pretty cool Teej.  You're the hostest with the mostest
nice yup, atving is becoming like snowmobiling clubs were  and forums bring even more of them together
Yer a flirt.LOL  NICE.
HMMMM, all them people now know the way to camp Jiggy!!!!! There'll never be a Carling left in the fridge when I show up again...
You never know, someone may have some taste.
Dont have the status to say that but was thinking it....  I will shut up now.

Nobody could find the place originally... TJ wasn't even sure if he could get to it by ATV when he bought the lot. Now there's a beaten trail... already had an outboard stolen... and now a herd to the door. TJ... please put a lock on the fridge and hid the key somewhere!!!
... and some flyboy dropped in on him, then posted the photos on the net.
LOL... but if you can find it by that method I wish you luck. I had the coords and almost gave up...
Party Time Very Cooool, looks like a nice feast SBK
looks like we need to have a tourny
Here Here.
Looks like fun I know that a dodge Caravan can NOT make it into Jiggy but it could make it close to the trail where one would off load a atv.

'Twas only a matter of time. You're both very welcoming, entertaining folks. Sounds like a party and a half, Bud. Thanks for the pics. The next time, there'll be a bonus in it for you if you include a pic of Monique.

Im not worried about anyone finding thioer way back in!! Our little campo was quite appreciated after the rain they were riding in...  http://www.atvnation.com/forum/index.php?showtopic=35522&st=255&p=340787entry340787
From the sounds of it your probably out of fish...Im sure it wont take the better half too much time to replenish the stock for the next wave of guests..  Good on ya for the hospitality
cool
Very Nice TJ! That fish looked awesome and I even saw some MGD beer on the table. Can't get much better than that!
So now can we name camp Jiggity Jiggity Ummpa Loompa Ville???   Art
